  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pain relapse during oral refeeding occurs in at least one-fifth of patients with acute
      pancreatitis. The study hypothesis is that early administered enteral tube feeding might
      reduce a risk of pain relapse and shorten the length of hospital stay in patients with acute
      pancreatitis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
